ce than the JMFAR. The good performance and low\ncomputational cost of JMFAR-ns supports the feasibility of using this algorithm\nvariant for real-time implementation in low-cost embedded systems. The method\npresented within this publication is protected by a pending patent application:\nAR P20220100910.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 1 Apr 2022 10:15:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 15 Nov 2022 22:52:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-17"}
